# Fluff Date: 2026-02-17 21:27:18
overview:<p>The Penthesilea was completed in early 3083 as the heaviest BattleMech ever produced by the Magistracy of Canopus. Designed by Majesty Metals and Manufacturing at their Dunianshire facility, the seventy-five-ton 'Mech was named after an Amazon queen of Greek mythology who fought to protect Troy. The design was born from political necessity as much as military need, with nearly all Magistracy weapons production concentrated on Detroit under tenuous political control, the Magestrix sought to diversify manufacturing to worlds firmly under her authority. The same team responsible for the Eyleuka was tasked with creating the heaviest 'Mech the Magistracy had ever fielded, intended to serve as a heavy fire support platform capable of engaging at multiple range brackets. The fragile peace following the Jihad provided the political cover to approve the project, simultaneously strengthening military capabilities and spreading advanced manufacturing knowledge beyond Detroit.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Penthesilea balances offensive and defensive capabilities through careful engineering trade-offs. A complex Dynastic 75-P endo steel frame and twelve tons of Maximillian 42F ferro-fibrous armor provide a solid protective foundation, while a compact gyro paired with a standard Vlar 300 fusion engine enhances pilot survivability, a longstanding Magistracy Armed Forces tradition. The design's sixty-four kilometer per hour top speed is modest for a heavy 'Mech, but three Nike Doublejet 9s jump jets providing ninety meters of jump capability offer valuable tactical repositioning.</p><p>The weapons array enables the Penthesilea to function as both sniper and brawler. A Majesty Metals Royal Flush extended-range PPC and Deuce light PPC deliver effective long-range harassment, while an Imperator Code Red LB-10X autocannon offers versatility through selectable solid slugs for armor penetration or cluster munitions for exploiting breaches. Three Diverse Optics Type II extended-range medium lasers round out the close-range arsenal. The primary drawback is heat management, thirteen double heat sinks struggle to dissipate the full weapons suite's output, demanding careful fire discipline from MechWarriors. CASE protection in the right torso mitigates the risk posed by the autocannon's ammunition bay.</p>

deployment:<p>Introduced in 3085, this variant represents Majesty Metals' effort to create a heavier-hitting Penthesilea for the Magistracy Armed Forces. The LB-10X autocannon is replaced with a devastating LB-20X model and the light PPC gives way to an ER large laser, dramatically increasing close-to-medium range lethality at the cost of some versatility. Two of the three ER medium lasers were removed to accommodate the larger autocannon, with the remaining laser relocated to the head. The compact gyro was exchanged for an extralight model to free tonnage, and the jump jets were sacrificed in favor of an additional heat sink. Protection was enhanced by replacing the standard ferro-fibrous armor with light ferro-fibrous plating. These changes transform the Penthesilea from a flexible fire support platform into a more focused brawler optimized for devastating close-range engagements.</p>

history:<p>The Penthesilea emerged from political tensions surrounding Magistracy of Canopus weapons manufacturing in the early post-Jihad period. With the vast majority of military production concentrated on Detroit (a world under tenuous Magistracy control) pressure mounted from two directions. Reactionaries were wary of relying on a politically vulnerable manufacturing base, while Majesty Metals and Manufacturing sought to expand production and profit from the advanced technology that had helped transform the Magistracy Armed Forces. The end of the Jihad brought a fragile peace that allowed the Magestrix to authorize the project, gaining political capital while strengthening the realm's industrial base on Dunianshire.</p><p>The first Penthesilea units rolled off the Dunianshire assembly line in 3083 and were sold to the mercenary command Zeus' Thunderbolts for field testing. Despite the unit's conspicuously reflective paint scheme making them impossible to miss, combat testing validated the design as an effective fire support platform. The jump jets, initially questioned by some critics, proved their worth by enabling rapid repositioning to optimal sniping positions and traversal of otherwise impassable terrain.</p><p>Once full production commenced, approximately half the output was assigned to elite Magistracy formations including the Royal Guard and the Chasseurs á Cheval regiments. Machines replaced by the new Penthesilea in both units were transferred to the Chasseurs. The remaining production was earmarked for export to allied Periphery nations and loyal mercenary commands. The Taurian Concordat became the first foreign customer approved for shipments, with Protector Boris Tharn rushing the new 'Mechs to Concordat units stationed in Federated Suns space to form the backbone of TDF fire support lances in the Pleiades region.</p><p>By the Late Republic era, the Penthesilea continued to evolve. A new variant was spotted with Canopian Lancers deployed on Pleione, Second Try, and Yunnah, supporting Capellan Confederation Mortis formations. This experimental redesign, incorporating actuator enhancement systems and a bombast laser, demonstrated the continued investment by Majesty Metals in expanding the Penthesilea's capabilities, even as the resulting design drew criticism for lacking a coherent tactical purpose.</p>

